        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><BR>I brought my friends monkey down here to get him some levels and crescent armor at the church. We set up in the crypt room -- you can get two non-aggro nibblers to spawn here. There is usually one nibbler in there when you start, we killed the second spawn in our rotation of the church spawns until it came up a nibbler.</P><P>Summoned and augmented a pet, and I kept my own buffs spaced at 15 minutes for ease of renewal. Had root, lifetap, vamp curse, Screaming Terror, Asystole, renew bones, augment death, and FD memmed. Would swap out random spells in the augment slot as nescesary.</P><P>With your pet in the crypt room, you can almost always run back to the boner before the caster mobs will toss a nuke your way because of the intervening wall, AND you have more time to spam Pet Back Off before he aggros the rest of the church. Normal single pull of greens, but since the monkey was only level 29 they were all good experience for him. Root, back the pet off and ST, let the monkey finish them to get the exp plus the dungeon bonus :></P><P>Recently the crescent armor drops have been reduce to a tiny trickle, which is rather unfortunate. However, ever since then I always try to take a friend's alt with me on long camps, gets them levels and gives me someone to talk with.</P><P>-- <BR>Life is a zero sum game, the only way to win is not to play.</P><P>Edited by - Israfel on 03/23/2001  16:41:26</font></td>
