        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>My new dagger and I thank you for the great guide.  No problem at 45.</P><P>Notes...</P><P>The Imprecator on the second floor shows up in the cubby on the west side of the room, not the south side.</P><P>I used a pet to save a bit on mana, and it worked pretty well.  Pull with darkness, /pet attack, watch the show.  Thanks to the recent aggro changes, once mobs were on the pet they pretty much ignored me, letting me meditate in peace.  Getting the best pet helped <b>a lot</b>.  The lowest pet could get pretty banged up by the casters, and the two lowest pets didn't kill things quickly enough for my liking.</P><P>Getting non-aggro roamers on the third floor helps a lot in the church/blacksmith area.</P><P>Church area gave me some bad pulls for no apparent reason.  Pet was a couple of rooms back, in the crypt room or the room beyond that around the corner, so that wasn't it.  I could single pull the church pretty reliably, but one evening it was the 5-for-1 special over and over.  Weird.  I also couldn't pull singles from the altar area without clearing the main area first, so I had to keep the whole church clear.  Which wasn't a problem, I just didn't have time to do the Blacksmith at the same time.</P><P>Only one death, when I discovered that the invokers can chain cast a 250-point DD when they're in the mood.  I stayed over half health after that.</P><P>When I set up in the lab, the only time I aggro'd the hall wanderer was when the bookcase mob showed up as a caster and my pet fought him right at the doorway.  Two at a time wasn't a problem.</P><P>Second floor piece took about half an hour, Blacksmith about two hours, church maybe six to eight hours over a couple of evenings, and lab another six to eight over a couple of days.  It can feel long waiting for specific drops, but it's not bad at all compared to some of the other silly quests out there.</P><P>Even if you don't get the piece you need in a particular camp, you don't go home empty-handed.  I typically went to the bank after each camp session with about 200 pp in platinum, gold, and fine steel.  I also averaged about two to three "bonus" drops per session, including a Sarnak Emblazened Tabard, Ketchata Koro Mis, Robe of the Foci, and the left-handed claw thing.  I think I also saw about two full sets of Crescent rot because there were either no monks, or the monks wouldn't come to the third floor to get it.  (Don't they sell invisibility potions in Cabilis?)</P><P>All in all, a fun time and a nice upgrade.</P><P><b>Morty Undercrypt</b>, Keeper of the <font color=red>NecroGnomicon</font id=red><BR><small>"Whoops, was I supposed to be taking names too?"</small><BR>E'ci</font></td>
